author: COMSOL
description: In a polymerization reactor for polyester manufacturing, the mixing in the reactor is achieved by impinging turbulent jets of reactants onto each other. The turbulence affects the reaction kinetics and quality of the polymer linkage. This example models the polymerization reactor at nonisothermal conditions using the Reacting Flow and Heat Transfer in Fluids interfaces.
